Introduction

Park Woojin is a South Korean rapper, dancer, songwriter, and composer under Brand New Music. He is best known as the main rapper and main dancer of the boy group AB6IX. He is also a former member of the project boy group Wanna One.

In 2017, Woojin participated in the second season of Mnet's survival television show, Produce 101, along with four other trainees from his agency, Brand New Music. He and Daehwi were the only ones to make it to the final line-up, ranking 6th and 3rd, respectively, becoming members of the boy group Wanna One.

On August 7, 2017, Woojin debuted in Wanna One with the mini album "1X1=1 (To Be One)" and its title track, "Energetic".

After the disbandment of Wanna One on January 27, 2019, Woojin was revealed as a member of Brand New Music's new boy group, AB6IX, which consisted of all four trainees of Produce 101 and another trainee from the agency. The group debuted on May 22, 2019 with the mini album "B:COMPLETE" and its title track, "Breathe". Before their official debut, a performance video of the track "Hollywood" was released on April 25, 2019.

On February 27, 2023, Woojin made his solo debut with the EP "Own".
